FIXES APPLIED:

Fix 1 — Re-entrant checkBadges() guard (js/xp.js)
  Added _checkingBadges boolean guard variable (initialized false).
  Wrapped checkBadges() body in if (_checkingBadges) return / try/finally block.
  Prevents cascading badge grant loops where _grantBadge -> awardXP -> checkBadges
  could theoretically re-enter checkBadges before the previous loop completes.

Fix 2 — console.warn for invalid awardXP amounts (js/xp.js)
  Added console.warn inside the early-return guard of awardXP().
  Warning fires for any invalid (non-zero) amount: negative, NaN, null, undefined.
  Suppresses warning when amount is exactly 0 (intentional no-op call pattern).
  Message format: [CyberSpark] awardXP called with invalid amount: X (reason: Y)

Fix 3 — Replace inline onclick with addEventListener in nav.js
  Removed onclick="window.location.href='index.html'" from persona-chip span in renderNav().
  Added separate block after hamburger event listener that queries #persona-chip
  and attaches click -> window.location.href = 'index.html' via addEventListener.
  Eliminates inline event handler, consistent with CSP best practices.

Fix 4 — Replace innerHTML with textContent for dynamic values (js/xp.js + index.html)
  _showBadgeToast (js/xp.js): Replaced toast.innerHTML template literal with
  explicit createElement('div') for toast-title and toast-body, set via textContent.
  selectPersona toast (index.html): Same pattern — replaced toast.innerHTML with
  toastTitle and toastBody elements set via textContent.
  Eliminates XSS risk if badge names/descriptions or persona data contain < > & characters.

Fix 5 — JSDoc Public API section updated (js/xp.js)
  Added awardPromptCopyXP(), markPageVisited(filename), and XP_AWARDS to the
  Public API documentation block at the top of xp.js.
  All entries aligned with consistent spacing for readability.

